fields.descriptive_line: A wallpaper pattern design, from a pattern book containing 206 specimens (E.1274-1479-1980) of colour prints from wood blocks, engraved rollers etc; Produced by John Line & Sons; England; 1880.
fields.physical_description: Pattern book of wallpaper designs containing 206 specimens (E.1274-1479-1980), some others have been torn out; Inscribed in ink inside the front cover The first pattern book issued by John Line & Sons. 1880. Bath. Reading. LHDayes Custodian 213-216 Tottenham Court Rd London W1 etc; each stamped on the back with trademark, serial number etc; Colour prints from wood blocks, engraved rollers etc.
fields.dimensions: Height: 26 cm size of volume, Width: 40.5 cm size of volume
